🚀 Getting Started

Prerequisites


A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
Node.js 18+ and npm — only if your project uses a build step


Installation


Clone the repository


bash   git clone https://github.com/your-username/todo-list.git
   cd todo-list


Install dependencies (skip if it's plain HTML/CSS/JS)


bash   npm install


Run the app
For a build-based project:


bash   npm run dev

Then open the URL shown in your terminal (usually http://localhost:5173).

For a plain HTML project, just open index.html in your browser.


📖 Usage


Type a task into the input field and press Enter (or click Add).
Click the checkbox next to a task to mark it complete.
Use the filter buttons to view All, Active, or Completed tasks.
Click the edit icon to rename a task, or the trash icon to delete it.
Use Clear Completed to remove all finished tasks at once.



